<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3108> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3108" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Att. 12.5b; Off. 3.109; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 468f. ([Sex.] Atilius M. f. C. n. Serran[us]); Obseq. 25; Chr. 354 (Pilo et Serrano); Fast. Hyd. (Philo et Servilio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Furius, Val. Max. 3.7.5. The Consuls carried the measure to surrender Mancinus to the Numantines (Cic. Off. 3.109), and Furius brought him to Hither Spain, but accomplished little in the war (Cic. Off. 3.109; Rep. 3.28; App. Ib. 83; Dio fr. 79, and 81; cf. Liv. Per. 56; and see Schulten, Gesch. Numantia 80f.). Atilius held command in Italy and Gaul (see 135, Promagistrates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3108 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3107> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3107" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The praenomen L. appears in Cicero (Brut. 108; Off. 3.109; Rep. 1.17) and Obsequens (25). P. in Val. Max. 3.7.5 and Cassiod. is almost certainly an error." ;
	dprr:hasID 3107 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3083> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3083" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest date possible for his praetorship." ;
	dprr:hasID 3083 .
